transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, hi. Did you say Viagra?

Speaker 1: Yes. Scor-Blue Viagra?

Speaker 2: Yeah. Is this Scor-Blue?

Speaker 1: Yes, Scor-Blue.

Speaker 2: Okay. Yeah, I just wanted to check. I usually call on an as-needed basis.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I thought I recalled the last time I spoke to someone, they said they were going to send pills in February.

Speaker 1: But I just want to check the status. I don't want – I want to do it on an as-needed basis.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no problem, Joe. Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: Sure. It's 11-11-68.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: I see you're a VIP customer. Yeah, you have it paused for five months until April 1st.

Speaker 2: Do you just want to get a refill and then I'll pause it again for you?

Speaker 1: Yeah. Actually, I don't need anything, so I was just trying to make sure they didn't send me anything in February or April.

Speaker 2: Sure. I'll pause you again until July 31st, so just put that in your calendar.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: No problem. Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too, Barbara.

Speaker 2: Bye.
